alue":"Show HN: Orbit \u2013 AR satellite tracker, watch 15k+ objects"},"url":{"fullyHighlighted":false,"matchLevel":"full","matchedWords":["rag"],"value":"https://<em>nag</em>ylukas.github.io/orbit.html"}},"_tags":["story","author_lukas9","story_48873501","show_hn"],"author":"lukas9","children":[48875844,48876800,48877038,48876023,48874856,48876410,48878231,48875789,48874454,48874959,48876475],"created_at":"2026-07-11T16:39:02Z","created_at_i":1783787942,"num_comments":19,"objectID":"48873501","points":85,"story_id":48873501,"story_text":"Hey HN! I made Orbit, an iOS app that allows you to see the satellites, planets, and constellations above you in AR, on a 2D map, and on a 3D globe.\nThe app includes more than 15,000 objects tracked by CelesTrack, together with their pass predictions, descriptions, and detailed orbital data.\nA searchable catalog of all objects is also available, as well as a built-in chatbot designed to answer any space-related questions you might have.<p>This is my first published iOS app, so any feedback is greatly appreciated!\nApp Store: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;apps.apple.com&#x2F;app&#x2F;id6772174570\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;apps.apple.com&#x2F;app&#x2F;id6772174570</a>","title":"Show HN: Orbit \u2013 AR satellite tracker, watch 15k+ objects","updated_at":"2026-07-13T10:32:14Z","url":"https://nagylukas.github.io/orbit.html"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"_samt_"},"story_text":{"fullyHighlighted":false,"matchLevel":"full","matchedWords":["rag"],"value":"Hi HN,<p>clx is an ahead-of-time compiler for standard Lua that generates C++20 and produces standalone native executables through GCC, Clang or MSVC.<p>The project started as an experiment to see whether modern C++ could be used as a portable compiler backend instead of LLVM or direct machine code generation. The generated code is then compiled and optimized by the host toolchain.<p>The latest release replaces the previous NaN-<em>tag</em>ged value representation with a new shadow-types implementation, adds full int64 support, improves native arithmetic code generation and adds ARM64 macOS coroutine support.<p>Performance is typically much faster than the Lua interpreter and can outperform LuaJIT on some computation-heavy workloads while remaining fully ahead-of-time compiled.<p>The repository also contains graphical examples written in Lua, including a Pong game and a Mandelbrot explorer using a Sokol binary module (using the clx C++ API)<p>I'd be very interested in feedback on clx :)"},"title":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"Show HN: Clx \u2013 Compile Lua to Native Executables Through C++20"},"url":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"https://github.com/samyeyo/clx"}},"_tags":["story","author__samt_","story_48871547","show_hn"],"author":"_samt_","created_at":"2026-07-11T12:40:24Z","created_at_i":1783773624,"num_comments":0,"objectID":"48871547","points":65,"story_id":48871547,"story_text":"Hi HN,<p>clx is an ahead-of-time compiler for standard Lua that generates C++20 and produces standalone native executables through GCC, Clang or MSVC.<p>The project started as an experiment to see whether modern C++ could be used as a portable compiler backend instead of LLVM or direct machine code generation. The generated code is then compiled and optimized by the host toolchain.<p>The latest release replaces the previous NaN-tagged value representation with a new shadow-types implementation, adds full int64 support, improves native arithmetic code generation and adds ARM64 macOS coroutine support.<p>Performance is typically much faster than the Lua interpreter and can outperform LuaJIT on some computation-heavy workloads while remaining fully ahead-of-time compiled.<p>The repository also contains graphical examples written in Lua, including a Pong game and a Mandelbrot explorer using a Sokol binary module (using the clx C++ API)<p>I&#x27;d be very interested in feedback on clx :)","title":"Show HN: Clx \u2013 Compile Lua to Native Executables Through C++20","updated_at":"2026-07-12T18:03:40Z","url":"https://github.com/samyeyo/clx"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"pjmlp"},"title":{"fullyHighlighted":false,"matchLevel":"full","matchedWords":["rag"],"value":"Microsoft latest report shows 25% emissions <em>rai</em>sed due to AI data centers"},"url":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"https://www.windowscentral.com/microsoft/dropping-greenwashing-credits-and-expanding-ai-datacenters-caused-microsofts-25-percent-emissions-jump"}},"_tags":["story","author_pjmlp","story_48870229"],"author":"pjmlp","children":[48872567,48871698,48871701],"created_at":"2026-07-11T09:10:45Z","created_at_i":1783761045,"num_comments":21,"objectID":"48870229","points":53,"story_id":48870229,"title":"Microsoft latest report shows 25% emissions raised due to AI data centers","updated_at":"2026-07-12T23:08:57Z","url":"https://www.windowscentral.com/microsoft/dropping-greenwashing-credits-and-expanding-ai-datacenters-caused-microsofts-25-percent-emissions-jump"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"cui"},"title":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"FreeCAD in the Browser"},"url":{"fullyHighlighted":false,"matchLevel":"full","matchedWords":["rag"],"value":"https://<em>mag</em>ik.net/freecad/"}},"_tags":["story","author_cui","story_48867264"],"author":"cui","children":[48867741,48867914,48867549,48867519,48867624,48867648,48867893],"created_at":"2026-07-11T00:44:00Z","created_at_i":1783730640,"num_comments":36,"objectID":"48867264","points":51,"story_id":48867264,"title":"FreeCAD in the Browser","updated_at":"2026-07-13T01:59:26Z","url":"https://magik.net/freecad/"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"fullyHighlighted":false,"matchLevel":"full","matchedWords":["rag"],"value":"<em>tag</em>awa"},"title":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"Count Binface, Nigel Farage's sp